    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2002-03-19", 
    "text": "COPS Anti-Methamphetamine Act of 2002 - Directs the Attorney General to make competitive grants to State and local community policing programs aimed at anti-methamphetamine enforcement, production, prevention, treatment, training, and intelligence gathering efforts.Provides assistance from the Community Oriented Policing Services Office in the Department of Justice.Earmarks at least 50 percent of funding for local community policing programs serving populations of not more than150,000."
